Package: bootconf
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Boot-time configuration tool for readonly Linux systems
 Reads a YAML configuration file and applies system settings at boot:
 hostname, timezone, SSH keys, WiFi, user accounts, and file provisioning.
 Designed for readonly OS appliances that need first-boot configuration.
